<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Merribelle</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-12-03 23:18:51</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The avvy is a great way to spend 32 - 35 =) one of the all time funnest camps on record. <BR>
<BR>
The avatar sees through Invis cast by equal or lower level casters but not higher, I believe. He does NOT see through rogue sneak / hide. I've done CR from under his very toes with sneak / hide up and never been seen.<BR>
<BR>
There are four spawns in the water above the bubble, generally judicators / justicars / zealots / fanatics. There are two spawns in the bubble itself, the Avatar or his PH (who is generally either Champion, Crusader or Zealot), and Cenobyte or his PH, a random high level lizard. Cenobyte / ph leaves the bubble immediately and will wander around the floor near the bubble.<BR>
<BR>
There is one wandering spawn that moves from the bubble, back up the hall to the door to the "safe" room and back down. While nothing spawns in the safe room mobs HAVE wandered through there due to bad pathing.<BR>
<BR>
You can invis and swim down through the bubble if the Avvy is not up, you can even leave that way under the same circumstances. If you're a rogue, you can sneak / hide / swim DOWN fairly safely but you won't be able to leave the bubble if you try to swim UP. <BR>
<BR>
Fighting  the Avatar will not agro those in the water  above him but if they are casters they'll heal him constantly. Clearing the pool is a good idea and gives you something to do in between 28 min spawns. The exp is good right up to 35.<BR>
<BR>
Fighting the avatar himself is not that difficult; have a tank or pet eat the HT - it hurts but generally by the time you hunt here you'll have enough HP to cope with it. A magic resist buff is a good idea to help ward off the fear spell he casts. If he's wielding claws he'll be VERY quick to hit you, and doesn't seem to fall for evade often. Roots and DoT's sometimes stick, especially if you have a chanter / shaman to malise / tashan, and anything that keeps those hp going down steadily is a benefit.  If you get an additional mob that isn't a caster, have someone root it out of the way or mez it. You REALLY can't afford to have more than the Avvy beating on you.<BR>
<BR>
Lastly, the drops. The claws are a good fast little slash weapon that are much underestimated. For those tanks who need to keep taunt off their casters, any fast weapon has a much greater taunt than your heavy slow axe, and the damage should pan out close to even because you are hitting much more often. <BR>
<BR>
The ravenscale BP is probably the single most sought after piece of rogue armor before level 46. Because of this people have a tendency to go "greed before need" and random it rather than give it to a rogue in the group who needs it. The average price on it is now around 1k though statistically it is only slightly better than a brigandine tunic, which sells as low as 500pp. I hope all of you will be honorable enough to hand this across to the people who need it, and not be like the avatar group I was with, who said "Any other piece of ravenscale and it's yours. But this BP is worth too much money"... *sigh*<BR>
<BR>
- Merribelle Stealshearts<BR>
Rogue Waif of 48 seasons<BR>
Hundred Companions of Bristlebane<BR>
<BR>
